A MANHUNT has been launched for a man believed to be involved in a rape incident that happened on 3 January 2023 at Spooktown in Bekkersdal, Gauteng. Police spokeswoman Linkie Lefakane said according to the information received, a 19-year-old woman was enjoying herself with friends when a man asked to talk to her outside. She allegedly went out with him but while outside, the man became aggressive. “He dragged her in the dark streets of Spooktown to a nearby bridge where he allegedly forcibly penetrated her,” said Lefakane. Fortunately, she managed to escape and reported the matter to the police. The victim was able to identify the suspect by means of an identity kit. “He is said to be 30-35 years of age, Sesotho speaking, short and chubby. He was wearing grey soccer pants, a white T-shirt with orange stripes, a black hat and brown boots. He was armed with a broken beer bottle,” said Lefakane. You must be SIGNED IN to read comments Police are urging SunReaders to come forward with any information that might help put the man behind bars. “Anyone with information about the suspect may contact Bekkersdal SAPS on 011 755 8069/8040 or CrimeStop on 08600 10111. Alternatively, they may contact the investigating officer, Detective Constable Rudzani Mushoma on 082 778 9048,” said Lefakane. The mother of the victim is pleading with SunReaders to help her get justice for her daughter. She said her daughter hasn’t been well since the incident.